⊢ sort
  given items[] ≡ [5, 3, 8, 1, 9, 2, 7, 4, 6]
  yield sorted[]

  ∴ Sort «items» in ascending order.

  ⊨ sorted is in ascending order
  ⊨ sorted has same length as «items»
  ⊨ sorted is a permutation of «items»

⊢ verify
  given sort→sorted
  given original[] ≡ [5, 3, 8, 1, 9, 2, 7, 4, 6]
  yield ok, violations[]

  ∴ Check that «sort→sorted» is correct:
    1. Every element ≤ the next element.
    2. Contains exactly the same elements as «original».
    Report ok=true if both hold, otherwise list violations.

  ⊨ ok is a boolean
  ⊨ if ok then violations is empty
  ⊨ if not ok then each violation describes a specific failure
